I then tried to activate AGE in a third computer, my htpc/gaming pc that has windows 7_x64 and is the only machine that's wired to the network and surprise: It activated like a charm.

Lastly just to be sure, I tried activating in the two windows 8.1 machines again using the cables that connected the htpc and had no luck.

data.title: Update Duktape to latest master
Project needs to be opened in the editor to create cache directories before --project can be used
data.body: If a project file is opened using the --project argument on the editor executable, it fails if that project has not first been opened using the editor's Open Project menu option. It appears that required cache directories are not created in this case. This scenario can happen when one team member creates the project, and another opens if after cloning a repository (since the cache directories are ignored in source control).
